<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-18T08:54:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-18T08:54:00-05:00" n="812" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d812">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.24/9–1844: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Appointed Minister to Saudi Arabia</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-18T17:00:00+03:06">September 18, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 11:21 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>282. ReDepts 177, September 12, 5 p.m. Today British colleague<note n="61" xml:id="d812fn61">Robert B. Ellison, British
                                    Chargé.</note> and I jointly notified King of 10,000–ton
                                increase in 1944 grain subsidy supply.</p>
                            <p>British colleague also has instructions to notify King of (1) extra
                                food supply for 1944 pilgrimage as listed in Legation’s 270, Sept.
                                8, 2 p.m. and (2) offer to stock food reserves at Jidda under
                                conditions stated in Legation’s 274, September 10, noon. Request
                                similar instructions.<note n="62" xml:id="d812fn62">In telegram 200,
                                    September 30, 7 p.m., the Minister was informed as follows: “You
                                    are authorized jointly with your British colleague to notify
                                    King Ibn Saud of authorization for additional food supplies for
                                    the pilgrimage in 1944, as described in your 270, September 8, 2
                                    p.m.” (890F.24/9–1844)</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>Repeated Cairo for AEMME.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Eddy</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>